DOCUMENT();
loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);
 
Context("Numeric");

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(2,7,1);
$u0 = random(1,8,1);
$nu0i = ( $u0 == 1 ) ? "-1" : "{-1\over $u0}";

$au0 = $a*$u0;
$u0d = ( $u0 == 1 ) ? '' : $u0;

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT

Find the solution to the differential equation
\[ $a {du\over dt} = u^2, \]
subject to the initial conditions \( u(0)=$u0 \).

$PAR
\( u = \) \{ ans_rule(35) \}

END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

ANS(fun_cmp( "$a*$u0/($a - $u0*t)", 'var'=>['t'] ) );

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR

Separating variables gives
\[ \int {1\over u^{2}} du = \int {1\over $a} dt\]
or
\[-{1\over u} = {1\over $a} t + C.\]

The initial condition gives \(C=$nu0i\) and so, after rearranging
slightly, 
\[ u={$au0\over $a - $u0d t}.\]

END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;


;
